title: Geolocation by Magnetic Field
text: GeoMag R package estimate animal geolocation using magnetic field data. provides tools robust calibration, outlier removal, likelihood map computation, interactive 3D visualization magnetic acceleration data. GeoMag designed work seamlessly GeoPressureR, enabling high-resolution migratory track reconstruction using multi-sensor archival tags.

title: Geolocation by Magnetic Field
text: GeoMag implements robust workflow geolocation based magnetic field measurements, including: Calibration: Correct sensor biases, scale factors, rotations using situ external datasets. Outlier removal: Automatically detect exclude spurious measurements. Likelihood mapping: Compute spatial likelihood maps using World Magnetic Model (WMM), comparing observed predicted intensity inclination. Interactive visualization: Explore raw calibrated data, ellipsoid fits, 3D scatterplots.

title: Geolocation by Magnetic Field
text: Magnetic sensor calibration (including ellipsoid sphere fitting) Likelihood mapping stationary periods (geomag_map) Integration GeoPressureR tag analysis workflow Interactive 3D plotting sensor data (plot_mag) Support WMM-based reference maps

title: Calibrate Magnetic and Acceleration Data for 3-Axis Sensors ‚Äî geomag_calib
text: Performs tilt compensation magnetic calibration 3-axis sensor data, support situ vitro calibration routines, outlier removal, computation orientation field parameters. function designed use GeoPressureR tag objects can utilize calibration datasets available.

title: Calibrate Magnetic and Acceleration Data for 3-Axis Sensors ‚Äî geomag_calib
text: Determine static/movement states: Classify data point static moving evaluating acceleration signals. Magnetic Data Calibration: Select calibration data source (raw calibration dataset). Optionally remove extreme outlier values. Fit apply calibration model (sphere/ellipse stap variants). Tilt Compensation: Compute pitch roll acceleration. Project gravity calibrated magnetic data horizontal plane Earth frame. Orientation Field Parameters: Calculate heading, field intensity, inclination. Store calibration metadata processed data tag object.

code: geomag_calib(   tag,   calib_data = NULL,   calib_method = NULL,   rm_outlier = TRUE,   quiet = FALSE )

title: Calibrate Magnetic and Acceleration Data for 3-Axis Sensors ‚Äî geomag_calib
text: tag GeoPressureR tag object containing magnetic acceleration data. calib_data Logical, character, NULL. TRUE, uses calibration data magCalib/ subfolder. FALSE, calibrates using situ data. character path, uses calibration data specified directory. NULL, auto-detects calibration folder. calib_method Character. Calibration method, one "sphere", "ellipse", "near-sphere", "sphere_stap", "ellipse_stap". NULL, chosen automatically. rm_outlier Logical. TRUE, removes outliers calibration data (recommended). quiet Logical. TRUE, suppresses progress messages.

title: Calibrate Magnetic and Acceleration Data for 3-Axis Sensors ‚Äî geomag_calib
text: Modified GeoPressureR tag object. $magnetic data frame contains: date: Timestamp (POSIXct numeric) acceleration_x, acceleration_y, acceleration_z: Raw acceleration data magnetic_x, magnetic_y, magnetic_z: Raw magnetic data is_static: Scaled MAD acceleration (0 = static, >1 = movement) pitch, roll: Orientation angles (radian) acceleration_xp, acceleration_yp, acceleration_zp: Gravity projected NED frame is_outlier: Logical, marks outliers magnetic data magnetic_xc, magnetic_yc, magnetic_zc: Calibrated magnetic data magnetic_xcp, magnetic_ycp, magnetic_zcp: Calibrated magnetic data projected NED frame H: Heading (radian, North=0) F: Magnetic field intensity (Gauss) : Inclination (radian) Also returns (invisibly) calibration dataset used (tag$mag_calib) calibration parameters (tag$param$geomag_calib).

code: geomag_map(   tag,   compute_known = FALSE,   sd_e_f = 0.007,   sd_e_i = 5,   sd_m_f = 0.01,   sd_m_i = 3.2,   ref_map = geomag_map_ref(tag),   quiet = FALSE )

title: Compute Magnetic Likelihood Maps ‚Äî geomag_map
text: tag GeoPressureR tag object . compute_known Logical. TRUE, computes likelihood maps known stationary periods; FALSE, fixes likelihood known location. sd_e_f Numeric. Standard deviation observation noise intensity error (single value one per stap). sd_e_i Numeric. Standard deviation observation noise inclination error (single value one per stap). sd_m_f Numeric. Standard deviation stationary-period-specific noise intensity error (single value per stap). sd_m_i Numeric. Standard deviation stationary-period-specific noise inclination error (single value per stap). ref_map Raster stack list. Reference magnetic maps (intensity inclination) computed default using geomag_map_ref(). Provide already computed save computational time. quiet Logical. TRUE, suppresses progress messages.

what: Interactive Visualization of Magnetic and Acceleration Data ‚Äî plot_mag
title: Interactive Visualization of Magnetic and Acceleration Data ‚Äî plot_mag
text: Provides interactive 3D 2D plots exploring GeoPressureR tag object sensor data, including raw calibrated magnetic data, fitted calibration ellipsoids, (projected) acceleration data. Color-coding stationary period movement state supported. Also supports time series histogram error plots reference paths. Plot types: "magnetic": Raw magnetic data sensor frame, colored stationary period. "calib": Calibration points fitted ellipsoids selected periods. "acceleration": Raw acceleration, colored static/moving classification. "acceleration_p": Projected acceleration (NED frame), reference gravity. "timeseries": Time series inclination intensity, optional reference path overlay. "histogram": Histogram errors (sample mean per stationary period) reference path.
